Police in Baringo yesterday burned 18 gambling machines in Kabarnet town. County commissioner Henry Wafula said the move will end the increased cases of troubles in families caused by gambling. “The operation will continue to ensure all gambling machines are destroyed,” Wafula said. The swoop will be conducted in Baringo North, South, Central, Mogotio, Tiaty and Eldama Ravine. The county commissioner said measures are in place to ensure the law is followed. “Be assured any person found trading with the gambling machines will be arrested and stern action will be taken against them,” he said, adding that gambling has become a worrying trend. 